r any family of class VII\nsurfaces whose generic fiber is a blown up primary Hopf surface. This statement\nwould have important consequences for the classification of class VII surfaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Dec 2010 16:56:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 5 Oct 2011 07:02:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-10-06"}
